Date wound up: If applicable, enter the date that the Superannuation Fund ceased operations if it was wound up during the year.

Trustee, director or public officer's contact person- First name: Enter the first or given name of the preferred contact- trustee, director or public officer of the fund. This is a mandatory field.
Trustee, director or public officer's contact person- Given name
Tax agent - Suffix: If applicable, enter the suffix of the tax agent for the fund.

Trustee, director or public officer's contact person- Other given names: If applicable, enter the second or subsequent names of the preferred contact- trustee, director or public officer of the fund.

Superannuation fund Trustee, director or public officer's contact person- Person Name Type Code: The person name type code should be set to LGL for Legal name. This is a mandatory field.
Trustee, director or public officer's contact person- name type code
Tax agent title: Enter the title of the tax agent for the fund.
Tax agent's contact person - title
Trustee, director or public officer's contact person- Title: Enter the title of the preferred contact- trustee, director or public officer of the fund.
Trustee, director or public officer's contact person- Title

Current postal address of superannuation fund/trust - Country

Superannuation fund Trustee, director or public officer's Declaration Statement Type Code: The declaration statement type code should be set to TrueAndCorrect. This is a mandatory field.
Trustee, director or public officer's declaration statement type code

Superannuation fund Tax agent's Declaration Signatory Identifier: The identifier used can be specified by the ABR credential owner providing it allows identification. Examples of suitable identifiers include a user login, a full name or an E-mail address. This is a mandatory field.
Tax agent's declaration signatory identifier text

Superannuation fund Trustee, director or public officer's Declaration Signatory Identifier: The identifier used can be specified by the ABR credential owner providing it allows identification. Examples of suitable identifiers include a user login, a full name or an E-mail address. This is a mandatory field.
Trustee, director or public officer's declaration signatory identifier text
Tax Agent declaration date: Enter the date (day, month, year) that the Tax Agent signed the signature field of the Declaration section. This is a mandatory field.

Trustee, director or public officer's declaration date: Enter the date (day, month, year) that the Director or Trustee signed the signature field of the Declaration section. This is a mandatory field.

If the declaration is not accepted then set the field to FALSE. This is a mandatory field.
Trustee, director or public officer's declaration statement accepted indicator
Tax Agent declaration: Enter the signature of the tax agent.
Tax Agent declaration statement text
Trustee, director or public officer's declaration: Enter the signature of either the trustee or director whichever one is appropriate.
Trustee, director or public officer's declaration statement text

Hours taken to prepare and complete this form: Enter the total time taken by the trustee and tax agent spent in preparing and completing the fund annual return. The time spent should be rounded up to the nearest hour. This field should also include the time spent by any other person who helped to complete the form.
Hours taken to prepare and complete this form
Year of return: Enter the the financial year or income year which the information provided in the report refers to. This is a mandatory field.
The year the Fund income tax return relates to

Bank State Branch number: Enter the Bank State Branch (BSB) code. Bank account details now need to be provided each year. Complete the BSB, Account number and Account name boxes. This is a mandatory field.
Bank State Branch number

Account name: Enter the name of the financial account that the client has elected to receive payments such as refunds or credits. Bank account details now need to be provided anew each year. Complete the BSB, Account number and Account name boxes. Enter the account name, as shown on the account records. Do not enter the account type â€“ for example savings, cheque or mortgage offset. Include spaces between each word and between initials in the account name. Joint accounts are acceptable. The account name must not exceed 32 characters.
Account name

Account number: Enter the bank account number. Bank account details now need to be provided anew each year. Complete the BSB, Account number and Account name boxes. Do not include spaces in the account number. This is a mandatory field.
Account number
Financial Institution branch name: Enter the branch name of the financial institution
Financial Institution branch name
Financial institution name: Enter the name of the financial institution
Financial Institution name
Australian Business Number: Enter the Australian Business Number (ABN) of the Superannuation Fund if applicable.
Australian Business Number of superannuation fund or trust
ABN of trustee: Enter the Australian Business Number (ABN) of the individual or company of the Superannuation Fund.
Australian business number of Non-individual trustee (if applicable)

Transfer of liabilities to a LIC or PST - ABN: If the answer to the transfer of liabilities question was Yes then enter the Australian Business Number (ABN) of the life insurance company or PST. This is a mandatory field.
Transferee Australian Business Number (ABN)- Transfer of liabilities to a Life Insurance Company (LIC) or Pooled Superannaution Trust (PST)
Client's reference: If applicable, enter the tax agentâ€™s reference number. This is the client number allocated by the tax agent to the fund.
Client's reference for the tax agent

Tax Agent number: Enter the Tax Agent Number (TAN). If the TAN consists of only seven digits, it is an old registration and it is necessary to add a â€˜0â€™ (zero) in front of the first four digits of the TAN.
Tax Agent number

Transfers from foreign funds: Enter all the assessable amounts transferred to an Australian superannuation fund from a foreign superannuation fund that were in excess of what was vested in the member at the time of the transfer. Include at this field amounts transferred to an Australian superannuation fund from a foreign fund by way of a written choice made by members of the fund .
Transferred from a foreign superannuation fund
Net capital gain: Enter the amount of the companyâ€™s net capital gain.
Net capital gain

Dividends - Franked amount: Enter the total amount of franked dividends and franked non-share dividends that the fund received, but do not include here franked amounts that the fund received from a New Zealand franking company. The franked part of a distribution from a Pooled Development Fund (PDF) is exempt from income tax, unless it is elected to include the amount in assessable income. In that case, the franked part of the distribution and the franking credit on the distribution worked out in accordance with the Income Tax Assessmant Act (ITAA) 1936, are included in assessable income. If the fund qualifies for a venture capital franking tax offset, the amount by which the venture capital franked part of a distribution from a PDF exceeds the franked part of that distribution is also exempt from income tax. This amount cannot be included in assessable income. However, a tax offset can be claimed in relation to a distribution franked with a venture capital credit even though the distribution is exempt from income tax.
Dividends - Franked amount

Trust distributions other amounts: Enter the total amount of gross distributions received from trusts that do not fall into any of the categories â€“ for example, amounts that are not dividends that were distributed to the fund from a trust. Include any amounts of interest income and rental income that were distributed to the fund from a trust. Include income received from a managed investment trust.
Trust distributions - income - other amounts

Capital works deductions: Enter the total deduction amount for qualifying capital works for an income year. Qualifying capital works are buildings (or an extension, alteration or improvement to a building), structural improvements (or extensions, alterations or improvements to structural improvements), and environmental protection earthworks, which have a construction expenditure area for which there is a pool of construction expenditure, and which the fund uses for the purpose of producing assessable income.
Capital works- Deductions
Forestry managed investment scheme deduction: Enter the total amount of deductible payments made to a Forestry Managed Investment Scheme (FMIS).
Forestry managed investment scheme - Deductions

Forestry managed investment scheme income: Enter the total income from all activities in the forestry interests that the fund holds in its Forestry Managed Investment Scheme (FMIS). The amount will depend on the activity. Activities include harvests and sales that are CGT events because these events result in the superannuation funds no longer holding some or all of its forestry interest. If the superannuation funds received thinning proceeds from its forestry interest, include the actual amount received . If the superannuation funds ceased holding its forestry interest as a result of a CGT event (because it sold its interest or it received harvest proceeds), include the market value of the forestry interest at the time of the CGT event. Sale and harvest receipts â€“ forestry interest still held If a CGT event happened and the superannuation funds still held its forestry interest (because it sold part of its interest or there was a partial harvest), include the amount by which the market value of the forestry interest was reduced. If the superannuation funds ceased holding its forestry interest as a result of a CGT event (because it sold its interest or it received harvest proceeds), include the lesser of the following two amounts, that is, either the market value of the forestry interest at the time of the CGT event, or the amount (if any) by which the total forestry scheme deductions exceeded the incidental forestry scheme receipts.
Forestry managed investment scheme income

Gross distribution from partnerships: Enter the gross distribution from all partnerships. If the distribution includes an amount of foreign income, including New Zealand franking company dividends and supplementary dividends, do not include that portion of the distribution at this label. Include it at Gross foreign income and take it into account in calculating Net foreign income. Include at this field any amounts subject to foreign resident withholding that were distributed to the fund from a partnership. Include the fundâ€™s share of credit from foreign resident withholding. A credit can be claimed for the fundâ€™s share of credit from foreign resident withholding in the calculation statement. If the amount calculated is a loss, print L in the Loss box at the right of the amount. If a distribution includes franked dividends (including franked non-share dividends), gross up the distribution to include any attached franking credit. If the fund is a complying superannuation fund, complying ADF or PST, write the amount of franking credit attached to such dividends at Credit- refundable franking credits. If your fund is a non-complying superannuation fund or non-complying ADF, include the amount of franking credits attached to such dividends at Rebates and offsets label. If family trust distribution tax (FTDT) has been paid on income received by the fund from partnerships, exclude that amount from the assessable income of the fund.
Gross distribution from partnerships

Gross rent and other leasing and hiring income: Enter all the rental income from land and buildings and all income from leasing and hiring. This item cannot be a loss. Do include in this field any rental income distributed from a trust, or income derived from foreign sources.
Gross rent and other leasing and hiring income
Taxable income/loss: Enter the the taxable income or loss amount by subtracting total deductions from total assessable income. This is a mandatory field.
Taxable income or loss
Other deductions: Enter the total amount of all other deductions that do not fall into any of the other categories.
Other deductions
Other deductions action code
Total TOFA losses: Enter all TOFA 3 & 4 losses sourced in Australia and overseas.
Total Taxation Of Financial Arrangements (TOFA) losses
Assessable income due to fund tax status change: Enter the amount that is to be included in the fundâ€™s assessable income as a result of a change in tax status of the fund.
Assessable income due to a change in tax status of the fund
Total TOFA gains: Enter all TOFA 3 & 4 gains sourced in Australia and overseas.
Total Taxation Of Financial Arrangements (TOFA) Gains

Gross foreign income: Enter the gross assessable income derived by the fund from foreign sources including New Zealand dividends and supplementary dividends. Do not include any Australian franking credits attached to New Zealand dividends. Include any income the fund received as a distribution of foreign source income from a partnership or trust.
Gross foreign income

Net non-arm's length income (subject to 45% tax rate): Enter the net amount of income that a superannuation fund, ADF or PST has received from a transaction or series of transactions between parties that is non-armâ€™s length income. This includes income such as private company dividends (including non-share dividends) certain distributions from trusts, and other excessive non-armâ€™s length income that is greater than might have been expected had it been derived from an armâ€™s length dealing.
Net amount of non-arm's length income (subject to 45% tax rate) received

Other income: Enter the assessable amount of any income received that does not fall into any of the other categories. Other income may include, but is not limited to foreign exchange (forex) gain, listed investment company (LIC) capital gain amount, assessable balancing adjustment amounts, rebate or refund of premium paid to provide death or disability benefits, gross payments subject to foreign resident withholding.
Other assessable income received

Trust distributions franked amount: Enter the total amount of franked dividends and franked non-share dividends included in trust distributions before grossing up the distributions to include any attached franking credits.Gross distributions from trusts may contain unfranked dividends, franked dividends, franking credits attached to these dividends, and other assessable distributions. Enter the amounts for the different components under distributions from trusts. Include any amounts subject to foreign resident withholding that were distributed to the fund from a trust. Also include the fundâ€™s share of credit from foreign resident withholding. All income received from stapled securities should be returned as trust distributions under the different components. This amount cannot be a loss. Enter whether any distributions received from a trust are part of a non-arm's length arrangement and whether the distribution received is greater than what might otherwise have been expected had the parties been dealing with each other at arm's length. If the distributions received are not at arm's length, do not include them under these distributions. Do not enter capital gains received from a trust at Trust distributions other amounts. Do not include distributions from PSTs under the trust distribution components. If FTDT has been paid on income or capital of a trust to which the fund is presently entitled or which has been distributed to the fund, exclude that income or capital from the assessable income of the fund.
Trust distributions - income - franked amount

Trust distributions unfranked amount: Enter the total amount of unfranked dividends and unfranked non-share dividends included in trust distributions. Gross distributions from trusts may contain unfranked dividends, franked dividends, franking credits attached to these dividends, and other assessable distributions. Enter the amounts for the different components under distributions from trusts.Include any amounts subject to foreign resident withholding that were distributed to the fund from a trust. Also include the fundâ€™s share of credit from foreign resident withholding.
Trust distributions - income - unfranked amount
Other assessable income received - code

Death or disability premiums: Enter the deduction for insurance premiums paid by a complying superannuation fund to provide superannuation benefits upon the death or temporary or permanent disability of the member.
Death or disability premiums - Deductions
Death benefit increase: Enter the increased amount of superannuation lump sum death benefits.
Death benefit increase deduction
Investment expenses: Enter the amount of expenses of a revenue nature incurred in deriving investment income, unless allowed by other specific income tax provisions.
Investment expenses
Interest expenses oversea: Enter the deductible interest incurred on money borrowed from overseas sources to acquire income-producing assets, finance operations, or meet current expenses.
Interest expenses overseas - Deductions
Interest expenses within Australia: Enter the deductible interest incurred on money borrowed from Australian sources to acquire income-producing assets, finance operations, or meet current expenses.
Interest expenses within Australia - Deductions

TOFA balancing adjustment: Enter the amount of the TOFA balancing adjustment. Where a taxpayer makes the transitional election to bring in their existing financial arrangements they must perform a balancing adjustment calculation. This amount will be used to calculate a TOFA taxpayer's PAYG instalment income.
Taxation Of Financial Arrangements (TOFA) balancing adjustment

Dividends - Unfranked amount: Enter the total amount of unfranked dividends and unfranked non-share dividends that the fund received. Do not include the unfranked distributions from a New Zealand franking company or the unfranked part of a distribution from a Pooled Development Fund (PDF). The unfranked part of the distribution is exempt from income tax and is not included in the fundâ€™s assessable income. However, this amount of exempt income must be taken into account when working out the amount of a tax loss.
Dividends - Unfranked amount

Show at 'Administration expenses' field the amount of expenses of a revenue nature incurred in the administration of the SMSF, unless the expense is more appropriately shown at another label. Do not include the expense of the approved auditor at Q. This expense should be shown at H Approved auditor fee.
Administration expenses
Credit- interest on early payments: Enter the calculated interest amount of 50 cents or more for early payments. Do not show payment amounts.
Credit for interest on early payments - amount of interest

The amount of expenses of a revenue nature incurred in the management of the SMSF, unless the expense is more appropriately shown at another label. Do not include investment management expenses. These expenses should be shown at I Investment Expenses.
Management expenses

Gross interest: Enter the total interest from all sources received by the fund. This item cannot be a loss. Do not include at this field non-share dividends received from holding a non-share equity interest. If the fund holds such an interest, the issuer is obliged to forward a dividend statement with details of the dividends, which should be written at unfranked dividend amount, franked dividend amount and dividend franking credit under income as applicable. Do not include at this field interest distributed from a trust, rental income distributed from a trust, or income derived from foreign sources.
Gross interest
Attributed foreign income - Listed country: Enter the amount of attributed foreign income from controlled foreign entities and transferor trusts in listed countries.
Attributed foreign income - Listed country - Foreign income and net assets
Attributed foreign income - Section 404 country: Enter the amount of attributed income from controlled foreign entities in section 404 countries.
Attributed foreign income in Section 404 countries.

Attributed foreign income - Unlisted country: Enter the amount of attributed foreign income from controlled foreign entities and transferor trusts in unlisted countries (excluding section 404 countries).
Attributed foreign income in Unlisted countries, excluding section 404 countries.
Credit - foreign income tax offset: Enter the self-determined amount that is the lesser of the foreign tax paid (or taken to have been paid), and it's foreign income tax offset limit.
Foreign income tax offset

Contributions excluded by trustee: Enter the contributions the trustee of a public sector superannuation scheme, with the contributorâ€™s consent, chooses not to include in its assessable income. The amount of contributions that the choice can cover is limited to the sum of amounts covered by notices given by the trustee for superannuation benefits paid in the income year. The choice cannot be revoked or withdrawn. A choice cannot be made in relation to a public sector superannuation scheme that comes into operation after 5 September 2006. Contributions excluded by trustee is used to determine Assessable contributions.
Contributions excluded by trustee that contribute to the calculation of assessable contributions - income

Pre-1 July 1988 funding credits: Enter the amount that a complying superannuation fund chooses to reduce contributions that would otherwise be included in its assessable income, by applying that amount of available pre-1 July 1988 funding credits.
Pre-1 July 1988 funding credits amount that contribute to the calculation of assessable contributions - income

Australian superannuation fund: Set the field to TRUE if the Superannuation Fund meets the criteria that defines it as an Australian Superannuation Fund, therefore a complying superannuation fund. Set the field to FALSE if it does not meet this criteria. This is a mandatory field.
Is the complying superannuation fund an Australian superannuation fund?

Were payments made or benefits transferred to contributing employers and associates?: If the answer to this question is Yes then set the field to TRUE. Otherwise, set the field to FALSE. This is a mandatory field.

Were payments made or benefits transferred to contributing employers and associates that is included in the assessable income of the recipient under section 290-100 of the SPECIALIST LIABILITY RULES to the INCOME TAX ASSESSMENT Act 1997?

Assessable employer contributions: Enter the amount of total assessable income comprising contributions and payments received by a superannuation entity in the income year. This includes all contributions to provide superannuation benefits for someone else, including those paid by an employer to a complying superannuation fund or to a non-complying superannuation fund where that fund is an Australian superannuation fund.
Assessable employer contributions

Transfer of liability to LIC or PST: Enter the amount of income otherwise assessable for the income year, that the trustee of a complying superannuation fund or a complying approved deposit fund (the â€˜transferorâ€™) has agreed to transfer to a life insurance company or PST (the â€˜transfereeâ€™) in which the fund holds investments.
Transfer of liability to Life Insurance Company or Pooled Superannaution Trust

Assessable personal contributions: Enter the total assessable amount of personal contributions. The trustee of a fund is to treat personal contributions as assessable contributions only if the contributor has provided a valid notice stating their intent to claim a deduction for their contributions.
Assessable personal contributions
No TFN quoted contributions: Enter all employer contributions received for a member who has not quoted a Tax File Number (TFN).
No -TFN quoted contributions

For Fund Benefit Structure, enter the appropriate code that best describes the benefit structure of the SMSF. The accepted codes are: A - Accumulation Fund D - Defined Benefit Fund U - Unfunded Defined Benefit E - A Hybrid Fund
This is a mandatory field.
Fund benefit structure

Has the actuary's certificate been obtained where exempt current pension income has been claimed?: If the answer to this question is Yes then set the field to TRUE. Otherwise set the field to FALSE. If the answer is Yes, has the trustee obtained the relevant actuaryâ€™s certificate or certificates required by sections of the Income Tax Assessment Act (ITAA) 1997 before exemption can be claimed?
Has the actuary's certificate been obtained where exempt current pension income has been claimed?

The gross income of a complying superannuation fund or PST derived from assets held to provide for current 'pension liabilities' is exempt from income tax. You would have shown this gross income amount at Labels A â€“ U at item 10. To ensure that that income is not taxed, it is necessary to deduct an identical amount at Y. Do not reduce the exempt income shown at Y by the amount of expenses incurred in deriving that income. Doing so will understate the deductible amount of exempt current pension and will result in some of that income being subject to tax. Expenses incurred in gaining or producing exempt income are not deductible; those expenses should not be shown anywhere at item 11. For treatment of expenses incurred wholly or partly in producing assessable income, see deductions: â€¢ D Capital works deductions â€¢ E Deduction for decline in value of depreciating assets â€¢ I Investment expenses â€¢ J Management expenses â€¢ Q Administration expenses, and â€¢ L Other deductions. Pension liabilities are the fund's liabilities to pay superannuation income stream benefits. The exemption on current pension income applies to all funds currently paying pensions. It does not provide an automatic exemption of the fund's total income as certain conditions must be met to obtain an exemption. There are two methods by which the trustee of a fund can determine the exempt income shown at Y. Either one method or both methods may be used depending on the circumstances. Different conditions for claiming the exemption apply, depending on the method used. A fund is entitled to franking credits on franked dividends received, even when the dividends relate to current pension liabilities.
Exempt current pension income

Credit: Interest on no - TFN tax offset: Enter the amount of interst on the no-TFN tax offset. Interest on the no-TFN tax offset is only payable if all the following conditions are met: - a member of the fund provided their TFN to their employer before the end of an income year (the past year) - the employer was required by section 299C of the SISA to inform the fund of the individualâ€™s TFN by the end of the past year, but did not provide the TFN to the fund - as a result, the contributions made in respect of that member were no-TFN-quoted contributions in that past year - an amount of additional tax (which is the interest-bearing tax) that was payable in respect of the no-TFN-quoted contributions counts towards the no-TFN tax offset under Subdivision 295-J of the ITAA 1997 for an income year (the current year) for the fund - the no-TFN tax offset under that subdivision is applied when assessing the fund for the current year The interest is payable on each amount of interest-bearing tax Interest on tax that counts towards the no-TFN tax offset is calculated for the period between the later of: - the day on which the amount of interest-bearing tax was paid, or - the day by which the amount of interest-bearing tax was required to be paid, and - the date on which the fund lodges its tax return for the current year (which is deemed to be the date on which the current year assessment is made).
Credit for interest on no-TFN tax offset

Credit: refundable National rental affordability scheme tax offset: Enter the amount of the refundable National rental affordability scheme tax offset. The national rental affordability scheme (NRAS) is designed to encourage large-scale investment in affordable housing. The NRAS offers incentives to providers of new dwellings on the condition that they are rented to low and moderate income households at 20 per cent below market rates. The refundable tax offset is only available where the Housing Secretary from the Department of Families, Housing, Community Services and Indigenous Affairs has issued a certificate under the NRAS. In order to claim the offset in the current income year, the NRAS certificate must relate to the NRAS year comprising the period for the current income year.
National rental affordability scheme tax offset
